This paper deals with the security and privacy issues in Internet routing, which are closely related to the fields of network security (cs.NI) and cryptography (cs.CR). The authors also use data analysis and modeling techniques to evaluate the exposure of communications between different countries, which falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), social networks (cs.SI), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
